commit.message: Fix a parsing bug in the rules that would ignore the very first rule. See #23.
Release version 0.73.

Improve error reporting. Fixes #15.

 - Add an error message when the configuration file could not be found.
 - Log to stderr when running in the foreground.
Do not log to syslog when running in the foreground. Addresses #15.
Fix another IPv6 parsing issue. Addresses #20.
Refactor getaddrinfo error reporting.
Fix some hostnames (e.g. 123.example.com) being wrongfully parsed as IPv6.
Release version 0.72.
Fix a configuration parsing bug.
Fix Mac OS X build.
Release version 0.71.
Fix HTML documentation generation.
Prepare version 0.71.
Improve documentation.
Refactor code to avoid duplication.
Merge branch 'feature-ipv6-support' into main
Update changelog for upcoming version 0.71.
Properly release the lexer context after reading the configuration.
Fix a format string issue on Windows.
Fix deny/allow rules to support IPv6 addresses.
Remove all legacy IPv4 code.
Remove deprecated getAddress() function now that we use getaddrinfo() ubiquitously.
Allow connecting to remote IPv6 addresses.
Use getaddrinfo() to resolve source address.
Use sockaddr_storage for IPv6 compatibility.
Get rid of useless fromProtocol struct member.
Add a helper function to retrieve socket type from protocol.
Remove the protocolType enum in favour of IPPROTO_TCP/IPPROTO_UDP.
Add a helper function to retrieve port from addrinfo.
Fix getaddrinfo() hint initialisation issues.
